		</div><!-- .comment-author .vcard -->
		
		<div class="comment-body"><p>That has been done but it  adds cost.  The earth has to be compacted, graded, insulated.  The percentage of increased performance is very small as the home is already very efficient.  I can&#8217;t tell much difference in utility bills.  I&#8217;m sure there would have to be some gain but I suspect not much.  We normally apply urethane form to the outside of the shell and waterproof over that.</p>
</div>

